sentences.content: Why a reading companion is important
What are the key reading companion features

First and foremost, the reading companion reads along with the user by listening while the user reads aloud, recognizes and advances the current word to be spoken to the next word, waits for the correct word to be spoken and eventually states the word after prescribed retry counts or listening duration is exceeded.
The companion can also synthesize the text to the user in different ways by reciting the:
current word and advancing to the next word
current sentence upto the current word
In any of these modes, the current word can either stay unchanged or advanced to the next unrecited word.
Advance to next word after recitation
Recogizes and properly interprets components of dates, years, numbers, phone numbers, email addresses, acronyms, symbols.
Designed as a web app to run within a web browser.
Works on any browser that support ReactJS and Web Speech API. Windows/Chrome, Windows/Safari, Windows/Firefox
The motif and style that determines its look and feel of the application can be changed based on individual cascading stylesheets and internal application settings.
Supports recognition of alternate pronunciations based on regular expressions especially relevant for proper nouns.
Recites a word, up to a word in a sentence, inclusive or exclusive, a section, paragraph
